(361,239,10,2,0,'176.181.139.237',1402597338,0,1,1,1,1,'','comment changer le texte avant authentification root','[quote=&quot;etxeberrizahar&quot;:1kps3su8][i:1kps3su8]Un petit texte, et en dessous LOGINNS [/i:1kps3su8] \n\nLOGGINNS,   logis INN ou [u:1kps3su8][b:1kps3su8] login[/b:1kps3su8][/u:1kps3su8]?  \n\nCompare le [i:1kps3su8]petit texte, et en dessous LOGIN [/i:1kps3su8] à /etc/issue.\n\n$ cat /etc/issue\n\n$ man issue\n[code:1kps3su8] ISSUE(5)                                  Linux Programmer\'s Manual                                 ISSUE(5)\n\nNAME\n       issue - prelogin message and identification file\n\nDESCRIPTION\n       The  file  /etc/issue  is a text file which contains a message or system identification to be printed\n       before the login prompt&#46;  It may contain various @char and  \\char  sequences,  if  supported  by  the\n       getty-type program employed on the system&#46;\n\nFILES\n       /etc/issue\n\nSEE ALSO\n       motd(5), agetty(8), mingetty(8)\n\nCOLOPHON\n       This  page is part of release 3&#46;65 of the Linux man-pages project&#46;  A description of the project, and\n       information about reporting bugs, can be found at http&#58;//www&#46;kernel&#46;org/doc/man-pages/&#46;\n\nLinux                                            1993-07-24                                         ISSUE(5)[/code:1kps3su8][/quote:1kps3su8]\ncomment changer le texte avant authentification root','f321f778acb17830b8991ff20f1b942d',0,'4YA=','1kps3su8',1,0,'',0,0,0,1,0,'',0),
